  "body": "Looking at https://github.com/ethereum/tests/tree/develop/GeneralStateTests/stPreCompiledContracts, we don't seem to have a modexp-test for `modexp(0,0, nonzero)`.\r\n\r\nThis is an issue found in py-evm, by @guidovranken\r\n\r\n> base = 0\r\n> exponent = 0\r\n> modulo = 36565857650062845505118984243340780147025291371401019\r\n> \r\n> Geth returns 1, but py-evm returns 0.\r\n> \r\n> This happens because py-evm returns 0 as soon as it detects that base is 0: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/efa07f743db4437a2762dfcd05535177046507e7/eth/precompiles/modexp.py#L96\r\n> which is not correct for any (zero, zero, > 1) tuple for (base, exp, mod).\r\n> \r\n",
